modules.description: Provides functions for manipulating and inspecting private values within the system, including accessors and comparators. Works with custom data types that encapsulate sensitive information. Used to verify internal state consistency during test scenarios.

manages private value manipulation and inspection, enabling verification of internal state consistency through custom data type operations. It supports comparators and accessors for sensitive information, facilitating detailed system analysis. This allows developers to debug and validate complex data structures during testing. Examples include checking equality of encrypted fields or extracting hidden metadata for diagnostics.

Provides a domain-specific language for defining command-line interfaces, translating declarative specifications into executable commands for cmdliner, core.command, or climate. Operates on structured command definitions, including subcommands, options, and positional arguments. Used to generate robust, type-safe command-line tools with minimal boilerplate.

manages internal state verification through custom data operations, offering comparators and accessors for sensitive values. It handles encrypted field equality checks and metadata extraction for diagnostic purposes. Developers can inspect and validate complex data structures during testing. Examples include verifying consistency of private values and retrieving hidden information for analysis.
